---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import TrainingChart from '@/components/TrainingChart.astro';
import photo from '@/assets/veljko.JPG';
---

<Layout title="About — wekzs" description="QA Automation Engineer with 7+ years of experience.">
  <section class="page-about">
    <h1 class="gradient-title g-cyan">Test. Break. Repeat.</h1>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="bio">
        <p>
          <strong>Hey, I'm Veljko.</strong> Born and raised in Serbia, grew up in Belgrade.
          The moment I first touched a computer I kind of never looked back. Technology just
          clicked for me in a way not much else did.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm into a lot of things. Design catches my eye constantly, I game when I get the
          chance, and I genuinely enjoy digging into other people's code just to see how they
          solved things. Gaming is actually what pulled me toward testing in the first place.
          Once you notice one bug you start seeing them everywhere.
        </p>
        <p>
          Open source stuff fascinates me. I love that someone somewhere just decides to build
          something and shares it with the world. Outside of tech I watch a lot of movies, probably
          too many.
        </p>
      </div>

      <Image
        src={photo}
        alt="Veljko Aleksić"
        width={640}
        height={640}
        class="about-photo"
        draggable="false"
        oncontextmenu="return false"
      />
    </div>

    <h2>Bio</h2>
    <p class="bio-sub">The short version, if you need one.</p>

    <blockquote class="bio-quote" id="bio-text">
      Veljko Aleksić is a QA Engineer from Belgrade. Seven years of breaking software on purpose,
      from accessibility testing to leading teams to building automation from scratch. Currently
      at ECD.rs working on a crypto platform. Loves clean test suites almost as much as dark mode.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="bio-actions">
      <a href="/cv" class="bio-cv-btn">
        <span class="bio-cv-icons">
          <svg class="bio-cv-icon-file" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7Z"/><path d="M14 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4"/></svg>
          <svg class="bio-cv-icon-arrow" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </span>
        View CV
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="training-heading">The Other Chart</h2>
    <p class="bio-sub">
      Since 2025 I've been training seriously. Before that I was mostly counting bugs.
      Turns out reps work differently. Still figuring out the whole process but I'm in it.
    </p>
    <p class="bio-sub">
      I've been staring at charts since I started trading Bitcoin back in 2019. I genuinely
      love reading them, and I love building them even more. This one is just a different
      flavor. Instead of watching candles turn red, I get to watch the volume go up. Same
      obsession, healthier outcome. I keep it mostly for myself, as motivation to not let
      the numbers drop, but maybe it's useful for someone else too.
    </p>
    <TrainingChart />
  </section>
</Layout>

